result.execSummary:
The defendant Lannenus J Hutchins was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Lannenus J Hutchins is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Lannenus J Hutchins was found guilty of Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Concur to 13CF563. If after successfully completing probation, no new crimes that result in convictions and no ATR's, then after 2 yrs, Def can petition for early release of probation.
